> Evoke your favorite summertime memories—the smell of barbecue wafting through
> the warm evening air, crickets chirping, the sound of kids playing outdoors—
> with this delicious sandwich that's ready in just 10 minutes.

Wash and dry produce. Pat @Fully Cooked Chicken Breasts{8.6%ounce} dry with
#paper towels{}. Halve @Lime{1}. Thinly slice @Tomato{1} into rounds.

Halve and toast @Brioche Buns{2}. While buns are toasting, combine chicken,
@BBQ Sauce{4%tablespoon}, and a pinch of @Salt{} and @Pepper{} in a #medium
microwave-safe bowl{}. Cover with #plastic wrap{}; microwave until warmed
through, ~{45-60%seconds}.

In a second #medium bowl{}, combine @Shredded Red Cabbage{4%ounce},
juice from lime, @Sugar{1%teaspoon}, a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{}, and
a pinch of salt and pepper. Toss to combine.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon},
@Hot Smoked Paprika{1%teaspoon}(half of), a drizzle of olive oil, and
a pinch of salt.

Spread smoked paprika mayo on cut sides of each top bun; fill buns with
as much slaw and tomato as you like. Top with BBQ chicken and close
sandwiches. Serve with any remaining slaw and tomato on the side.